OL,3,CBlue cards and sin bins to be delayed
OL,4,Cafter talks with Fifa
OL,6,FThese are to be used by referees when
OL,7,Fthey feel threatened or intimidated
OL,8,Fand mean that once the zone has been
OL,9,Fcreated, only team captains should
OL,10,Fenter.
OL,12,FA further trial is understood to
OL,13,Fcentre on 'cooling-off' periods, where
OL,14,Fa referee sends teams to their penalty
OL,15,Fareas to calm down after a mass
OL,16,Fconfrontation, for example.
OL,18,FAnother trial will look at a new
OL,19,Fapproach to how long goalkeepers can
OL,20,Fhandle the ball, and how play should
OL,21,Frestart when they hold on too long.
